<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<appendix xml:id="app-chi-square-table">
  <title>The Chi-Square Distribution</title>

  <p>This appendix gives right-tail critical values for the <term>chi-square distribution<idx><h>appendices</h><h>chi-square table</h></idx></term>. Each entry <m>\chi^2_\alpha</m> satisfies <m>P(\chi^2 \gt \chi^2_\alpha)=\alpha</m> for the stated degrees of freedom.</p>
  <p>The left-side columns are useful for lower-tail cutoffs, while the right-side columns are the ones most often used for hypothesis tests and confidence intervals.</p>
  <p>To keep the print layout centered and readable, the columns are split into two related tables.</p>

